				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$$\:\text{\%}\:association=\:=\left(\frac{{{C}_{o}-C}_{supernatant}}{{C}_{o}}\right)100$$\end{document}where Co is the initial concentration of samples, and Csupernatant is the concentration of the supernatant of samples after the settling period.

The reduction in the abundance of bacteriophage (N) due to UV exposure can be described by the double-exponential model (Eq. (2)) as follows35:2\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym} 
