				\begin{document}$$\:N=\left(1-\beta\:\right){N}_{\text{o}}{e}^{-{k}_{1}{UV}_{Dose}\:}+\beta\:{N}_{\text{o}}{e}^{-{k}_{2}{UV}_{Dose}\:}$$\end{document}where, N is the residual concentration of culturable organisms after UV exposure, No is the initial number of culturable organisms in PFU-CFU/mL, and UVDose is the delivered UV Dose in mJ/cm2. In addition, β indicates the fraction of UV-resistant organisms, and finally k1, and k2 represent first-order inactivation rate constants for UV-susceptible and UV-resistance fractions, respectively. The use of a double-exponential model allows for the representation of tailing effects, or concavity to the dose-response model, that are commonly observed from UV disinfection.

The actual UV dose delivered to the samples can be calculated by Eq. (3)36. This calculation were made following the Bolton and Linden (2003) protocol37.3\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
